<img src="http://www.gravatar.com/avatar.php?gravatar_id=40324a65c60787a466eac93339353d75&amp;size=40" alt="" />
<h4 class="vcard"><span class="fn url"><a href="http://twitter.com/paulrandall">Paul Randall</a></span></h4>
<blockquote><p>A great writeup. I totally see the benefits of creating sites like this. There should be more conversation with the client as to why a 10 year-old browser cannot, and should not look exactly the same as the latest Safari or Firefox nightly build.</p>

<p>If we as designers try to make a pixel-perfect version in each browser, we are inevitable adding more work, creating bloated code and additional images to create the effects the modern browsers achieve so easily. We are doing a disservice to the client in the end.
</p></blockquote>

<p><time datetime="2009-06-27" class="updated published">27th Jun 2009 <span class='value-title' title="2009-06-27"></span></time>
<span class="origin"></span></p>
</li>

