<blockquote><p>Thanks everyone for your kind compliments. I really was more nervous about giving this talk than any other I&#8217;ve given. At An Event Apart in Boston, I was literally shaking!</p>

<p><a href="#r2119">@ Oisin Prendiville</a>: <em>However I do find it difficult to justify the notion, unless I have misunderstood it, that although these methods help us complete a job in a third time we should still be billing clients clients more hours and using that time to blog, learn new skills, and develop our own projects at their expense.</em></p>

<p>— The way I look at it is, my clients are neither paying me for the hours that I work, nor even what I make for them. Instead they are paying for a &#8216;solution&#8217; (I hate that word) to their business needs. I solve problems and enable their business to do what they need on line.
</p></blockquote>

